idCitation.resTitle: Solar Insolation for a Stream Network

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This tool applies a solar radiation surface to a stream network polyline feature class. The tool assumes that the stream network has been previously segmented. Solar insolation is summarized per stream network feature. The tools requires a solar radiation raster dataset produced by the first tool in the Solar Stream Tools toolbox, Generate Solar Insolation Surface.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: South Fork Research, Inc. Jesse Langdon

tool.name: SolarVectorTool
tool.displayname: Solar Insolation for a Stream Network

param.name: in_raster
param.dialogReference: Raster dataset representing solar insolation for the area encompassing a drainage network (units: W/hm2). This dataset should be a TIF file produced by the Generate Solar Insolation Surface tool.

param.name: in_stream
param.dialogReference: Polyline feature class representing a stream network of a drainage area.

param.name: in_strm_indx
param.dialogReference: An attribute field within the stream network polyline feature class that stores a unique identifier value for each stream reach feature.

param.name: in_strm_area
param.dialogReference: An attribute field within the stream network polyline feature class that stores a unique identifier value for each stream reach record.

param.name: out_fc
param.displayname: Output polyline feature with solar values
param.dialogReference: Polyline feature class that is generated by the tool. The feature class will have the same geometry as the input stream network, but with a new attribute field called "area_solar" which stores the summarized solar insolation values for each stream reach feature.

param.name: workspace_temp
param.dialogReference: Workspace (either a folder or a file geodatabase) for storing temporary data files produced by the tool.

param.name: rs_bool
param.dialogReference: Indicates if the tool's products will be used in a Riverscapes project. If the checkbox is activated, a user-specified workspace will be created which will store tool inputs and outpus, as well as an associated XML file (titled project.rs.xml). This and subsequent parameters are optional. The tool can be run successfully without be associated with a Riverscapes project.

param.name: rs_dir
param.dialogReference: Workspace which will store data inputs and outputs, as well as a project XML file (i.e. project.rs.xml).

param.name: rs_proj
param.dialogReference: Name of the Riverscape project. This parameter is for display purposes only, and will be automatically populated when an existing Riverscapes workspace is selected.

param.name: rs_real_name
param.dialogReference: Name of an existing realization within the selected Riverscapes project. This tool can only add to an existing realization within a project. If the project includes multiple realizations, all realizations will be available for selection as a dropdown list.
